The above code is a bit of a hack.  It works by spawning a thread that will listen for SIGWINCH signals.  When it receives a SIGWINCH signal, it will set the window size of the master process and the stderr master process (if there is one).  The stderr master process is the master process of the stderr of the process we're spawning.  This is because when we spawn a process, the stderr of that process is redirected to the
